

# **Multi-Class Image Classification Use Cases (Fun & Easy)**

### 1️⃣ Classroom Mood Detector – “Class Mood” (3 classes)

* **Class A:** Happy / engaged faces
* **Class B:** Bored / sleepy faces
* **Class C:** Confused / distracted faces
  Mini Engineers can act out all three moods — very expressive and fun.

### 2️⃣ Desk Setup Monitor – “Desk Type” (3 classes)

* **Class A:** Neat desk (laptop, notebook arranged)
* **Class B:** Messy desk (papers, books scattered)
* **Class C:** Minimalist desk (just essentials)
  Engineers can stage different “desk personalities” — neat, messy, or minimalist.

### 3️⃣ Classroom Activity Detector – “Student Activity” (4 classes)

* **Class A:** Writing / taking notes
* **Class B:** Listening / paying attention
* **Class C:** Raising hand / asking question
* **Class D:** Distracted / using phone
  Tech enthusiasts can act out all four behaviors — very relatable for classroom scenarios.

### 4️⃣ Online Exam Proctoring – “Student Behavior” (2 classes)

* **Class A:** Focused / looking at screen
* **Class B:** Distracted / suspicious behavior (looking away, using phone, notes, or other gadgets)
  Mini Engineers can act out both behaviors — “techy + school-related” and super fun to stage.

